Jerry Grayson was the youngest pilot to join the Royal Navy in 1972 . 
  He was involved in rescuing sailors during the Fastnet Yacht Race in 1979 . 
  The 59-year-old has tracked down every helicopter he flew in during the 1970s . 
  He travelled 23,000 miles to find one of the choppers converted into a glamping unit . 
  Mr Grayson joined the Navy at the age of 17 and was responsible for saving 15 yachtsmen during the race . 
  He joined the Fleet Air Arm and became a rescue pilot in the Navy . 
  He flew every aircraft he ever flew as part of Royal Navy rescue missions during the 70s . 
  The former pilot was once the youngest helicopter pilot in Britain . 
 